Here's a PlantUML sequence diagram representing the dynamic interactions of the Bytom Server system, focusing on performance and deployment aspects:

```plantuml
@startuml Bytom-Community_Bytom-Server

participant "Client" as C
participant "gRPC API" as API
participant "Transaction Pool" as TP
participant "Blockchain Core" as BC
participant "P2P Network" as P2P
participant "Bytom VM" as VM
participant "Data Store" as DS
participant "Mining Module" as MM

C -> API: Submit Transaction
activate API

API -> TP: Add Transaction
activate TP
TP -> BC: Validate Transaction
activate BC
BC -> VM: Execute Contract (if needed)
activate VM
VM --> BC: Execution Result
deactivate VM
BC --> TP: Validation Result
deactivate BC
TP --> API: Transaction Added
deactivate TP

API --> C: Transaction Accepted

P2P -> TP: Broadcast Transaction
activate P2P
TP -> BC: Process New Block
activate BC
BC -> DS: Store Block
activate DS
DS --> BC: Block Stored
deactivate DS
BC --> TP: Update UTXO Set
deactivate BC
TP --> P2P: Block Processed
deactivate P2P

MM -> BC: Generate Block Template
activate MM
BC --> MM: Block Template
MM -> BC: Submit New Block
BC -> P2P: Broadcast New Block
P2P --> BC: Block Propagated
BC --> MM: Block Accepted
deactivate MM

@enduml
```